            "master": 0.8,
            "sfx": []
          }
        },
        "notes": "\"If you're deciding which way to go, I suggest you come with us. There's nothing left of Highmoor; not for you, not for any of us.\"\n\n\nCan help with\t\nFood, warmth, and a friendly footing with the caravan\n\nReveals if asked\nThe pale-night story (Highmoor fell in a single night, no army, just cold and quiet and screaming) \nTales of the caravan's grief and hope\nFear that the city they are walking toward may not want them",
